{
  "texts": [
    "Counting-based supervision for auxiliary models can only be exploited once semantic evidence is sufficiently clear, so its effect is limited to later diffusion steps and to samples where object categories are already well formed.",
    "By contrast, ISAC strengthens instance structure at early timesteps, before semantics have fully emerged, by reshaping attention to separate and stabilize instance-level regions; this enables it to reach the highest counting accuracy without auxiliary networks [45] or extra labels such as instance-level mask annotations.Flexibility of ISAC Beyond the text-to-image setting in Tab. 2 and Tab.",
    "4 shows that ISAC also improves layout-to-image controllers [12].",
    "On HRS-Bench, ISAC yields the largest gains among layout refinements [37].",
    "This advantage comes from enforcing instance separation for adjacent boxes early in the diffusion trajectory, rather than only constraining attention within each box."
  ]
}